0with%20the%20audience.%20The%20lively%20and%20stylishly%20mounted%20exploration%20of%20contemporary%20relationships%20and%20social%20dynamics%20seen%20through%20the%20prism%20of%20urban%2C%20upper-class%2C%20extravagant%20marriages%20was%20always%20going%20to%20be%20a%20hard%20act%20to%20follow.%20Showrunners%20Zoya%20Akhtar%20and%20Reema%20Kagti%20pull%20it%20off%20with%20flair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESet%20in%20Delhi%2C%20where%20change%20rarely%20keeps%20up%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20life%20and%20conservatism%20and%20penumbral%20greys%20always%20lurk%20behind%20a%20facade%20of%20modernity%2C%20the%20seven%20new%20episodes%20centre%20on%20another%20slew%20of%20families%20and%20couples%20looking%20for%20unions%20of%20true%20minds%20-%20and%20souls%20-%20and%20straying%20into%20slippery%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETara%20Khanna%20(Sobhita%20Dhulipala)%20and%20Karan%20Mehra%20(Arjun%20Mathur)%20return%20to%20the%20business%20of%20planning%20weddings%20for%20an%20elite%20clientele.%20The%20initial%20feeling%20is%20that%20time%20has%20stood%20still%20for%20the%20two.%20Only%2C%20the%20constant%20tussle%20between%20the%20heart%20and%20the%20head%2C%20between%20principles%20and%20self-preservation%2C%20has%20turned%20that%20much%20more%20complex%20in%20the%20intervening%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20floundering%2C%20profits%20are%20proving%20to%20be%20elusive%2C%20big%20fat%20weddings%20of%20the%20kind%20that%20could%20turn%20things%20around%20are%20scarce%2C%20and%20the%20clients%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20small-scale%20their%20events%20are%2C%20are%20as%20demanding%20as%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20episodes%20directed%20by%20Nitya%20Mehra%20(one)%2C%20Alankrita%20Shrivastava%20(two)%2C%20Zoya%20Akhtar%20and%20Reema%20Kagti%20in%20tandem%20(two)%20and%20Neeraj%20Ghaywan%20(two)%2C%20much%20of%20the%20new%20season%20bears%20the%20signature%20that%20lent%20the%20inaugural%20lot%20of%20episodes%20their%20zing%20-%20a%20combination%20of%20style%2C%20earnestness%20and%20an%20occasional%20hint%20of%20subversion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20has%20changed%20for%20the%20series%2C%20created%20by%20Akhtar%20and%20Kagti%20and%20scripted%20by%20the%20duo%20with%20Shrivastava%2C%20is%20the%20addition%20of%20Ghaywan%20as%20a%20director.%20The%20maker%20of%20%3Ci%3EMasaan%3C%2Fi%3E%20helms%20two%20norm-defying%2C%20clutter-breaking%20episodes.%20Of%20course%2C%20part%20of%20the%20credit%20for%20the%20high%20notes%20must%20accrue%20to%20the%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Ghaywan's%20two%20episodes%20centres%20on%20the%20father%20of%20a%20bride%20and%20the%20mother%20of%20a%20groom%20who%20are%20in%20an%20extra-marital%20relationship%20that%20has%20rekindled%20a%20college%20romance%20and%20now%20threatens%20to%20derail%20the%20wedding%20of%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F_lpxWzvII5k%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20episode%2C%20radically%20different%20from%20anything%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20before%20on%20an%20OTT%20platform%2C%20features%20Pallavi%20Menke%20(Radhika%20Apte)%2C%20an%20Ivy%20League%20professor%2C%20who%2C%20when%20we%20first%20see%20her%2C%20spells%20out%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20a%20Dalit%20in%20India.%20We%20learn%20along%20the%20way%20that%20she%20has%20authored%20a%20book%20on%20the%20intersectionality%20of%20caste%20and%20gender.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20of%20the%20hotshot%20upper-caste%20NRI%20lawyer%20she%20is%20about%20to%20marry%20insists%20on%20a%20traditional%20ceremony.%20She%20agrees%2C%20but%20demands%20a%20Dalit%20Buddhist%20wedding%20in%20addition.%20Her%20wish%20sets%20the%20cat%20among%20the%20pigeons%20and%20triggers%20a%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20so%20much%20to%20learn%20from%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20impressed%20Tara%20says%20to%20the%20assertive%20Pallavi.%20She%20could%20well%20have%20paid%20the%20same%20compliment%20to%20Meher%20Chaudhary%2C%20a%20transgender%20woman%20(Trinetra%20Haldar)%20who%20works%20for%20her%20company.%20The%20latter%20objects%20vehemently%20when%20Tara%20calls%20the%20upper%20caste%20ceremony%20the%20%26quot%3Bmain%20wedding%26quot%3B.%20Tara%20is%20forced%20to%20take%20back%20the%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20of%20pushing%20boundaries%2C%20%3Ci%3EMIH%20S2%20%3C%2Fi%3E%20delves%20deeper%20into%20same-sex%20relationships%20and%20the%20assertion%20of%20sexual%20identities%20than%20it%20did%20the%20first%20time%20around%20and%2C%20even%20more%20strikingly%2C%20casts%20a%20transgender%20actor%20to%20play%20a%20career%20woman%20who%20has%20had%20a%20gender%20reassignment%20surgery%20and%20is%20proud%20of%20who%20she%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EMIH%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20like%20the%20first%20season%20did%2C%20addresses%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20themes.%20It%20concludes%20each%20chapter%20with%20an%20apt%20homily%20(it%20stops%20well%20short%20of%20being%20preachy)%20directed%20at%20women%20who%20allow%20societal%20expectations%20to%20snuff%20out%20their%20aspirations%20and%20desires.%20One%20episode%20focuses%20on%20a%20case%20of%20polygamy%20that%20tests%20the%20endurance%20of%20a%20Muslim%20woman%20(Dia%20Mirza)%20whose%20husband%20(Pravin%20Dabas)%20takes%20a%20second%20wife.%20Another%20episode%20revolves%20around%20a%20same-sex%20%26quot%3Bcommitment%20ceremony%26quot%3B%20involving%20two%20women%20battling%20prejudices%20like%20modern-day%20%26quot%3Bwarrior%20princesses%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAway%20from%20the%20subject%20of%20marital%20vows%20and%20discord%20-%20the%20latter%20is%20represented%20principally%20by%20the%20complicated%20divorce%20settlement%20negotiations%20between%20Adil%20Khanna%20(Jim%20Sarbh)%20and%20Tara%20-%20an%20important%20strand%20of%20%3Ci%3EMIH%20S2%3C%2Fi%3E%20revolves%20around%20a%2015-year-old%20schoolgirl%20(only%20mentioned%2C%20not%20seen)%20who%20accuses%20a%20handful%20of%20boys%20in%20her%20class%20of%20molesting%20and%20blackmailing%20her.%20How%20the%20parents%20react%20to%20the%20allegation%20forms%20the%20crux%20of%20this%20sub-plot.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20about-to-be-married%20girl%20breaks%20out%20in%20a%20rash%20after%20an%20ill-advised%20skin-lightening%20treatment%20goes%20awry%2C%20a%20divorced%20woman%20who%20is%20set%20to%20remarry%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20a%20depressed%20son%20who%20misses%20his%20father%20to%20the%20point%20of%20hating%20his%20mom%2C%20and%20a%20sprightly%2035-year-old%20woman%20(Sarah%20Jane%20Dias)%2C%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20plans%20to%20wed%20a%20much%20younger%20boy%20(Imaad%20Shah)%2C%20masterminds%20a%20twist%20in%20the%20tale%20that%20nobody%20sees%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20weddings%20that%20they%20handle%20pose%20their%20own%20share%20of%20problems%20and%20the%20company%20grapples%20with%20dwindling%20returns%20and%20internal%20contradictions%2C%20Tara%20and%20Karan%20are%20up%20against%20their%20own%20struggles.%20Tara%20has%20a%20new%20boyfriend%20in%20chef%20Raghav%20Sinha%20(Ishwak%20Singh)%20while%20contending%20with%20the%20aggravating%20presence%20of%20her%20one-time%20best%20friend%20and%20her%20estranged%20husband's%20lover%20Faiza%20Naqvi%20(Kalki%20Koechlin).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaran%2C%20still%20under%20a%20monetary%20debt%20that%20demands%20desperate%20measures%2C%20sees%20his%20relationship%20with%20his%20terminally%20ill%20mom%20souring%20drastically.%20Their%20individual%20flaws%20come%20to%20the%20fore%20as%20they%20try%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20the%20not-so-strong%20cards%20in%20their%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20Jauhari%20(Vijay%20Raaz)%2C%20from%20whose%20old%20bungalow%20the%20cash-strapped%20Made%20in%20Heaven%20now%20functions%2C%20sends%20in%20his%20wife%20Bulbul%20(Mona%20Singh%2C%20an%20addition%20to%20the%20cast)%20to%20oversee%20the%20expenses%20