20struggled%20for%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20struggle%20further%20escalated%20on%20August%205%20when%20Khan%20was%20sentenced%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20on%20corruption%20charges%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Intercept%20report.%20However%2C%20Khan's%20supporters%20have%20denied%20the%20charges%2C%20terming%20them%20baseless.%20The%20decision%20announced%20by%20the%20court%20also%20blocks%20Khan%20from%20contesting%20polls%20expected%20in%20Pakistan%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20month%20after%20the%20meeting%20with%20US%20officials%20was%20revealed%20in%20the%20Pakistan%20government's%20document%2C%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%20was%20held%20in%20Parliament%2C%20resulting%20in%20Khan's%20ouster%20from%20power.%20The%20vote%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20parliament%20was%20believed%20to%20have%20the%20support%20of%20Pakistan's%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vote%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20been%20organised%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20Pakistan's%20powerful%20military.%20Since%20his%20ouster%2C%20Khan%20and%20his%20supporters%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20a%20struggle%20with%20the%20army%20and%20its%20civilian%20allies%2C%20whom%20the%20former%20Pakistan%20PM%20engineered%20his%20removal%20from%20power%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%20last%20year%2C%20Pakistan's%20then-Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Kha%20raised%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20conspiracy%26quot%3B%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20nation%20amid%20his%20coalition%20government%20seemingly%20losing%20the%20majority%20after%20losing%20the%20support%20of%20some%20allies%2C%20Khan%20said%20a%20foreign%20power%20sent%20a%20message%20that%20he%20needs%20%26quot%3Bto%20be%20removed%26quot%3B%20or%20Pakistan%20will%20face%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20foreign%20nation%20sent%20a%20message%20to%20us%20(Pakistan)%20that%20Imran%20Khan%20needs%20to%20be%20removed%20else%20Pakistan%20will%20suffer%20consequences%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Referring%20to%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20conspiracy%20letter%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20its%20language%20%26quot%3Bwas%20threatening%20and%20arrogant%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2027%2C%20Khan%20had%20waved%20the%20%26quot%3Bletter%26quot%3B%20at%20a%20public%20rally%20saying%20a%20foreign%20conspiracy%20was%20afoot%20to%20oust%20him.%20He%20had%20sought%20to%20link%20the%20opposition's%20no-confidence%20motion%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bforeign-funded%26quot%3B%20move%20to%20topple%20his%20government.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20text%20of%20the%20Pakistani%20cable%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bcypher%26quot%3B%2C%20produced%20from%20the%20meeting%20by%20the%20ambassador%20and%20transmitted%20to%20Pakistan%20has%20revealed%20the%20methods%20used%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20in%20its%20push%20against%20Khan%2C%20promising%20warmer%20ties%20with%20Islamabad%20if%20Khan%20was%20removed%2C%20and%20isolation%20if%20he%20was%20not%2C%20The%20Intercept%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20document%2C%20titled%20'Secret'%2C%20includes%20an%20account%20of%20the%20meeting%20between%20US%20State%20Department%20officials%2C%20including%20Assistant%20Secretary%20of%20State%20for%20the%20Bureau%20of%20South%20and%20Central%20Asian%20Affairs%20Donald%20Lu%20and%20Asad%20Majeed%20Khan%2C%20who%20was%20then-Pakistan's%20ambassador%20to%20the%20US.%20An%20anonymous%20source%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20military%20has%20provided%20the%20document%20to%20The%20Intercept.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cable%20includes%20the%20carrots%20and%20sticks%20used%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20in%20its%20push%20against%20then-Pakistan%20PM%20Imran%20Khan.%20The%20dynamics%20of%20the%20Pakistan-US%20ties%20mentioned%20in%20the%20cable%20were%20subsequently%20borne%20out%20by%20events%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Intercept%20report.%20In%20the%20cable%2C%20the%20US%20has%20raised%20objections%20to%20the%20foreign%20policy%20of%20Imran%20Khan%20over%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict.%20The%20stance%20taken%20by%20Imran%20Khan%20over%20Ukraine%20was%20quickly%20reversed%20post%20his%20removal%20from%20office.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20diplomatic%20meeting%20between%20US%20State%20Department%20officials%20and%20the%20Pakistani%20government%20took%20place%20two%20weeks%20after%20the%20conflict%20between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20started%2C%20as%20Khan%20was%20heading%20to%20Moscow.%20Pakistani%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20(PTI)%20chairman%20Imran%20Khan's%20visit%20to%20Russia%20angered%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%2C%202022%2C%20just%20days%20before%20the%20meeting%2C%20Lu%20had%20been%20questioned%20at%20a%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20hearing%20over%20the%20neutral%20stance%20taken%20by%20Pakistan%20and%20other%20nations%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%20Responding%20to%20the%20question%20from%20Senator%20Chris%20Van%20Hollen%2C%20Lu%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20Khan%20has%20recently%20visited%20Moscow%2C%20and%20so%20I%20think%20we%20are%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20engage%20specifically%20with%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20following%20that%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20The%20Intercept%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20before%20the%20meeting%2C%20Khan%2C%20addressing%20a%20rally%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20we%20your%20slaves%3F%E2%80%9D%20He%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20think%20of%20us%3F%20That%20we%20are%20your%20slaves%20and%20that%20we%20will%20do%20whatever%20you%20ask%20of%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20In%20his%20remarks%2C%20then-Pakistan%20PM%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20friends%20of%20Russia%2C%20and%20we%20are%20also%20friends%20of%20the%20United%20States.%20We%20are%20friends%20of%20China%20and%20Europe.%20We%20are%20not%20part%20of%20any%20alliance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20document%2C%20Lu%2C%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%20expressed%20US'%20displeasure%20over%20Pakistan's%20position%20on%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELu%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20here%20and%20in%20Europe%20are%20quite%20concerned%20about%20why%20Pakistan%20is%20taking%20such%20an%20aggressively%20neutral%20position%20(on%20Ukraine)%2C%20if%20such%20a%20position%20is%20even%20possible.%20It%20does%20not%20seem%20such%20a%20neutral%20stand%20to%20us%26quot%3B%2C%20The%20Intercept%20quoted%20Lu%20as%20saying%20in%20the%20document.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELu%20further%20said%20that%20he%20had%20held%20internal%20discussions%20with%20the%20US%20National%20Security%20Council%20and%20it%20%26quot%3Bseems%20quite%20clear%20that%20this%20is%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20policy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%2C%20The%20Intercept%20quoted%20Donald%20Lu%20as%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20if%20the%20no-confidence%20vote%20against%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20succeeds%2C%20all%20will%20be%20forgiven%20in%20Washington%20because%20the%20Russia%20visit%20is%20being%20looked%20at%20as%20a%20decision%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20will%20be%20tough%20going%20ahead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELu%20had%20warned%20that%20Pakistan%20would%20be%20marginalised%20by%20its%20Western%20allies%20if%20the%20situation%20was%20not%20resolved.%20He%20had%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20tell%20how%20this%20will%20be%20seen%20by%20Europe%20but%20I%20suspect%20their%20reaction%20will%20be%20similar%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20Khan%20could%20face%20%E2%80%9Cisolation%E2%80%9D%20by%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%20should%20he%20remain%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20about%20Lu's%20quotes%20in%20the%20Pakistani%20cable%2C%20US%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%C2%A0Matthew%20Miller%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CNothing%20in%20these%20purported%20comments%20shows%20the%20United%20States%20taking%20a%20position%20on%20who%20the%20leader%20of%20Pakistan%20should%20be.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMiller%2C%20however%2C%20said%20he%20would%20not%20react%20to%20private%20diplomatic%20discussions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Pakistani%20ambassador%20voiced%20frustration%20with%20the%20lack%20of%20engagement%20from%20US%20leadership.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20reluctance%20had%20created%20a%20perception%20in%20Pakistan%20that%20we%20were%20being%20ignored%20or%20even%20taken%20for%20granted.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20feeling%20that%20while%20the%20US%20expected%20Pakistan's%20support%20on%20all%20issues%20that%20were%20important%20to%20the%20US%2C%20it%20did%20not%20reciprocate.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20document%2C%20the%20discussion%20concluded%20with%20the%20Pakistani%20ambassador%20expressing%20hope%20that%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20would%20not%20affect%20the%20bilateral%20ties%20between%20Islamabad%20and%20Washington.%20Lu%20had%20said%20the%20damage%20was%20real%20but%20not%20fatal%20and%20with%20Imran%20Khan%20gone%2C%20the%20ties%20could%20return%20to%20normal%2C%20The%20Intercept%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELu%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20argue%20that%20it%20has%20already%20created%20a%20dent%20in%20the%20relationship%20from%20our%20perspective.%26quot%3B%20He%20further%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet%20us%20wait%20for%20a%20few%20days%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20political%20situation%20changes%2C%20which%20would%20mean%20that%20we%20would%20not%20have%20a%20big%20disagreement%20about%20this%20issue%20and%20the%20dent%20would%20go%20away%20very%20quickly.%20Otherwise%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20confront%20this%20issue%20head%20on%20and%20decide%20how%20to%20manage%20it.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%208%2C%202022%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20meeting%2C%20Imran%20Khan's%20opponents%20in%20Parliament%20moved%20forward%20with%20procedural%20steps%20towards%20the%20no-confidence%20vote.%20The%20US%20State%20Department%20has%20previously%20and%20on%20repeated%20occasions%20denied%20that%20Lu%20urged%20the%20Pakistani%20government%20to%20remove%20Khan%20as%20Prime%20Minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%208%2C%202022%2C%20US%20State%20Department%20spokesperson%20Jalina%20Porter%2C%20responding%20to%20the%20allegations%20levelled%20by%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BLet%20me%20just%20say%20very%20bluntly%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20truth%20to%20these%20allegations%26quot%3B%2C%20The%20Intercept%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20month%20after%20the%20meeting%20was%20described%20in%20the%20cable%20and%20just%20days%20prior%20to%20Khan's%20ouster%20from%20power%2C%20Pakistan's%20then-army%20chief%20Qamar%20Javed%20Bajwa%20termed%20the%20Russian-Ukraine%20conflict%20a%20%E2%80%9Chuge%20tragedy%E2%80%9D%20and%20criticised%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20remarks%20backed%20the%20public%20picture%20with%20Lu's%20private%20observation%2C%20described%20in%20the%20cable%2C%20that%20Pakistan's%20neutrality%20over%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20was%20the%20policy%20of%20Khan%20and%20not%20of%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691634360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2Fia818iug_imran-khan-afp_625x300_19_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-state-department-encouraged-pakistan-government-to-remove-imran-khan-as-prime-minister-report-4284776%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20State%20Department%20in%20a%20meeting%20on%20March%207%2C%202022%20encouraged%20the%20Pakistani%20government%20to%20remove%20Imran%20Khan%20as%20the%20country's%20Prime%20Minister%20over%20his%20neutrality%20in%20the%20conflict%20between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20US-based%20news%20outlet%20The%20Intercept%20reported%22%2