-space-exploration-moon-mars-asteroids-comets-2020-10%5C%22%3Edeep-space%20exploration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20an%20open%20question%2C%20Lehnhardt%20said%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthe%20consequence%20of%20someone%20becoming%20pregnant%20in%20space%20could%20be%20very%20high.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20unfettered%20space%20fornication%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221087%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Starship%20spacecraft%20test%20flight%20in%20Texas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F641343710308e00018550f5f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22815%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Starship%20prototype%20launches%20from%20SpaceX's%20facilities%20in%20Boca%20Chica%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20not%20even%20be%20possible%20to%20get%20pregnant%20in%20space%2C%20but%20it's%20probably%20not%20worth%20taking%20the%20chance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20very%20little%20research%20on%20the%20effects%20the%20space%20environment%20might%20have%20on%20reproductive%20systems.%20That's%20partly%20because%20space%20research%20has%20long%20been%20dominated%20by%20government%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20NASA%20stays%20away%20from%20sex%20and%20reproduction%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehnhardt%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20truly%20relevant%20to%20the%20work%20that%20we're%20doing%20at%20NASA%20right%20now%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20it%20has%20been%20relevant%2C%20reproductive%20health%20hasn't%20been%20one%20of%20NASA's%20strong%20suits.%20Engineers%20there%20famously%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsally-ride-first-american-woman-in-space-life-legacy-2019-6%5C%22%3Eastronaut%20Sally%20Ride%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20100%20tampons%20would%20be%20enough%20for%20a%20one-week%20spaceflight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20space%20reproduction%20studies%20that%20do%20exist%20are%20focused%20on%20rodents.%20Their%20findings%20may%20not%20be%20applicable%20to%20humans%20at%20all%2C%20but%20they%20offer%20hints%20that%20reproductive%20functions%20could%20be%20affected%20by%20space%20radiation%20and%20microgravity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colonel%20Walter%20Villadei%20aboard%20Galactic%2001%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3ab8182eb770019b9062d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EColonel%20Walter%20Villadei%20floats%20in%20microgravity%20during%20a%20Virgin%20Galactic%20flight.%3Cp%3EVirgin%20Galactic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fnsr%2Farticle%2F7%2F9%2F1437%2F5819033%3Flogin%3Dfalse%23267959580%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20researchers%20put%20mouse%20embryos%20in%20an%20incubator%20on%20board%20a%20satellite.%20The%20embryos%20developed%20in%20space%20but%20sustained%20%26quot%3Bsevere%26quot%3B%20DNA%20damage%20and%20had%20developmental%20defects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dc36bbbfc6b6ba65038f24dad2830be619dba18ce4f0f5f96ab428388944151d6%26postID%3D646d4da3dff48323162199e6%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41574-019-0267-6%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20exposure%20to%20microgravity%20decreased%20testosterone%C2%A0levels%20and%20sperm%20production%20in%20male%20rats.%20Some%20female%20rats%20have%20mated%20during%20spaceflight%20but%20then%20shown%20signs%20of%20early%20pregnancy%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20forms%20of%20radiation%20on%20Earth%20are%20known%20to%20have%20negative%20effects%20on%20human%20pregnancy.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthe%20galactic%20cosmic%20radiation%20that%20we%20experience%20in%20space%20doesn't%20have%20a%20good%20comparison%20on%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20Lehnhardt%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20even%20be%20risky%20to%20conceive%20within%20a%20few%20months%20of%20returning%20from%20spaceflight%2C%C2%A0the%20green%20paper%20authors%20argue.%20Again%2C%20research%20is%20lacking.%20The%20uncertainty%20is%20enough%20for%20some%20astronauts%20to%20freeze%20their%20eggs%20before%20they%20launch%20into%20orbit%2C%20according%20to%20Lehnhardt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHave%20you%20talked%20to%20your%20spaceflight%20customers%20about%20sex%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222724%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22elon%20musk%20raises%20one%20eyebrow%20wearing%20a%20suit%20in%20as%20room%20full%20of%20seated%20men%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3a7d411d6ad0019edfba6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222043%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20at%20the%20%26quot%3BChoose%20France%26quot%3B%20Summit%20at%20the%20Chateau%20de%20Versailles%2C%20outside%20Paris.%3Cp%3ELudovic%20Marin%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20someone%20does%20get%20pregnant%20up%20there%2C%20that%20person%20or%20their%20fetus%20could%20face%20complications.%20Failure%20to%20address%20this%20possibility%20puts%20space-tourism%20companies%20at%20risk%20of%20reputational%20damage%20or%20litigation%2C%20the%20green%20paper%20argues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20definitely%20not%20trying%20to%20say%20you%20should%20ban%20sex%20in%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20David%20Cullen%2C%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20paper%20and%20a%20professor%20of%20space%20biotechnology%20at%20Cranfield%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20he%20continued%2C%20companies%20should%20%26quot%3Bput%20in%20place%20procedures%20and%20mitigations%20to%20minimize%20the%20chance%20of%20any%20sexual%20interactions%20leading%20to%20human%20conception.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECullen%20and%20his%20co-authors%20argue%20that%20space-tourism%20leaders%20should%20talk%20about%20the%20risks%20of%20acting%20on%20orbital%20arousal.%20Companies%20could%20require%20that%20their%20customers%20undergo%20medical%20and%20reproductive%20counseling%2C%20or%20sign%20waivers%20about%20sex%20and%20reproduction%20before%20flying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ETo%20build%20cities%20on%20other%20planets%2C%20we%20have%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20make%20babies%20out%20there%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20are%20just%20the%20first%20steps.%20If%20humans%20are%20to%20settle%20on%20other%20planets%20to%20become%20a%20%26quot%3Bmultiplanetary%20species%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20goal%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-china-censor-humans-multi-planetary-mars-spacex-2022-8%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20often%20touted%20over%20the%20years%20%E2%80%94%20someone%20will%20need%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20feasibility%20and%20risks%20of%20space%20sex%2C%20pregnancy%2C%20and%20birth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22elon%20musk%20holds%20his%20hands%20up%20palms%20out%20smiling%20wearing%20a%20suit%20in%20front%20of%20a%20wall%20with%20the%20logo%20viva%20technology%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3a8bc11d6ad0019edfd71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAs%20far%20as%20we%20know%2C%20SpaceX%20is%20not%20discussing%20sex%20with%20its%20spaceflight%20customers.%3Cp%3EGonzalo%20Fuentes%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Cullen%20and%20other%20authors%20of%20the%20paper%20are%20working%20on%20an%20initiative%20called%20SpaceBorn%20United%2C%20to%20research%20in%20vitro%20fertilization%20(IVF)%20in%20space.%20The%20company%20plans%20to%20try%20space%20IVF%20first%20using%20mouse%20embryos%2C%20in%202024%2C%20but%20eventually%20aims%20to%20test%20on%20human%20embyros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20are%20the%20stepping%20stones%20of%20research%20that%20would%20be%20needed%20to%20see%20how%20viable%20pregnancy%20could%20be%2