%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsyrias-president-assad-would-welcome-home-refugees-12936973%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Syrian%20President%20Bashar%20al%20Assad%20has%20said%20he%20would%20welcome%20home%20refugees%20who%20escaped%20the%20country's%20long-running%20civil%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fsyrias-president-assad-would-welcome-home-refugees-12936973%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsyrias-president-assad-would-welcome-home-refugees-12936973%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fsyrias-president-assad-would-welcome-home-refugees-12936973%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exclusive%3A%20A%20veteran%20FBI%20agent%20told%20Congress%20that%20investigations%20into%20Giuliani%20and%20other%20Trump%20allies%20were%20'suppressed'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FBI%20headquarters%20in%20Washington%20DC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3eb344dd2b50019c243c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20J.%20Edgar%20Hoover%20FBI%20Building%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Brandon%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAn%20FBI%20veteran%20said%20his%20superiors%20suppressed%20investigations%20of%20Trump%2C%20Insider%20can%20exclusively%20reveal.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BAre%20we%20going%20to%20do%20public%20corruption%20or%20not%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20whistleblower%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20his%20boss%20ordered%20him%20to%20stop%20investigating%20Giuliani%20and%20the%20Trump%20White%20House.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20veteran%20FBI%20counterintelligence%20agent%20says%20his%20supervisor%20told%20him%20to%20stop%20investigating%20Rudy%20Giuliani%20and%20to%20cut%20off%20contact%20with%20any%20sources%20who%20reported%20on%20corruption%20by%20associates%20of%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20according%20to%20a%20whistleblower%20complaint%20obtained%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agent%2C%20who%20served%2014%20years%20as%20a%20special%20agent%20for%20the%20bureau%2C%20including%20a%20long%20stint%20in%20Russia-focussed%20counter-intelligence%2C%20claims%20in%20a%2022-page%20statement%20that%20his%20bosses%20interfered%20with%20his%20work%20in%20%26quot%3Ba%20highly%20suspicious%20suppression%20of%20investigations%20and%20intelligence-gathering%26quot%3B%20aimed%20at%20protecting%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20politically%20active%20figures%20and%20possibly%20also%20FBI%20agents%26quot%3B%20who%20were%20connected%20to%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20oligarchs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20figures%2C%20the%20statement%20claims%2C%20explicitly%20included%20%26quot%3Banyone%20in%20the%20%5BTrump%5D%20White%20House%20and%20any%20former%20or%20current%20associates%20of%20President%20Trump.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%2C%20which%20was%20prepared%20for%20staffers%20of%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%2C%20was%20apparently%20leaked%20and%20posted%20in%20mid-July%20to%20a%20Substack%20newsletter.%20Insider%20has%20independently%20obtained%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20complaint%20and%20verified%20its%20authenticity%2C%20but%20has%20not%20corroborated%20all%20of%20its%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Insider%2C%20the%20whistleblower%20said%20he%20was%20motivated%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20improve%20the%20FBI%2C%20which%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bessential%2C%20as%20imperfect%20as%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20its%20sweeping%20power%20to%20hold%20%26quot%3Bpolicymakers%20accountable%2C%20whether%20they're%20on%20the%20left%20or%20the%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20decision%20point%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAre%20we%20going%20to%20do%20public%20corruption%20or%20not%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20is%20withholding%20the%20name%20of%20the%20whistleblower%20because%20he%20has%20made%20claims%20about%20retaliation%20from%20the%20FBI%2C%20where%20he%20remains%20an%20employee%2C%20and%20because%20he%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20seeking%20whistleblower%20protections%20from%20Congress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20highly%20unfortunate%20that%20this%20statement%20wound%20up%20being%20leaked%20and%20published%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Scott%20Horton%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20the%20whistleblower.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20the%20preliminary%20stages%20of%20a%20confidential%20process.%20I'm%20unable%20to%20make%20any%20other%20comment.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whistleblower%20told%20Insider%20that%20he%20was%20finally%20ordered%20to%20stop%20investigating%20Giuliani%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Trump%20White%20House%20in%20August%202022%2C%20after%20months%20of%20what%20he%20says%20were%20persistent%20efforts%20to%20frustrate%20his%20work%2C%20at%20a%20meeting%20with%20three%20FBI%20supervisors%20at%20a%20bureau%20field%20office.%20Insider%20was%20able%20to%20confirm%20the%20agent's%20account%20of%20the%20meeting%20with%20a%20second%20source%20with%20knowledge%20of%20what%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20had%20been%20called%20to%20discuss%20the%2014-year%20veteran's%20job%20performance.%20As%20one%20of%20the%20bureau's%20few%20Russian-speaking%20counterintelligence%20specialists%2C%20he%20maintained%20a%20network%20of%20overseas%20sources%20that%20had%20been%20utilized%20by%20agents%20across%20the%20country%20to%20investigate%20everything%20from%20money%20laundering%20to%20political%20corruption%2C%20according%20to%20his%20statement.%20He%20said%20his%20work%20had%20been%20recognised%20with%20eight%20consecutive%20years%20of%20%26quot%3Bexcellent%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Boutstanding%26quot%3B%20performance%20appraisal%20reports%20running%20from%202010%20to%202018%2C%C2%A0%20and%20he%20had%20been%20tapped%20to%20help%20verify%20information%20obtained%20by%20investigators%20working%20for%20Robert%20Mueller%20during%20his%20time%20as%20special%20counsel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20the%20August%202022%20meeting%2C%20he%20was%20called%20onto%20the%20carpet%20to%20discuss%20%26quot%3Bperformance%20issues%20and%20concerns%26quot%3B%20and%20given%20suggestions%20for%20how%20to%20improve%2C%20according%20to%20the%20agent's%20account%20provided%20to%20lawmakers.%20The%20directions%20he%20received%20included%20a%20strict%20prohibition%20on%20filing%20intelligence%20reports%20relating%20to%20Giuliani%20or%20any%20other%20Trump%20associate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20meeting%20was%20the%20culmination%20of%20what%20the%20agent%20viewed%20as%20a%20years-long%20effort%20to%20frustrate%20his%20investigations%20into%20potential%20wrong-doing%20by%20political%20figures%20in%20Trump's%20circle%2C%20stretching%20back%20to%20Trump's%20stint%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20In%20January%202022%2C%20he%20had%20filed%20an%20internal%20complaint%20under%20the%20Whistleblower%20Protection%20Act%20alleging%20%26quot%3Bnumerous%20acts%20of%20intelligence%20suppression%20of%20my%20reporting%20related%20ot%20foreign%20influence%20and%20the%20Capital%20riots%2C%20retaliatory%20acts%20and%20defamation%20of%20my%20own%20character.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23903968-wed-redact%2F%3Fembed%3D1%26responsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Whistleblower%20statement%20(Hosted%20by%20DocumentCloud)%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22895%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20case%2C%20the%20statement%20says%2C%20the%20agent%20developed%20information%20from%20confidential%20informants%20that%20Giuliani%20had%20allegedly%20done%20paid%20work%20for%20Pavel%20Fuks%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20oligarch%20and%20%26quot%3Basset%20of%20the%20Russian%20intelligence%20services.%26quot%3B%20(That%20charge%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rollingstone.com%2Fpolitics%2Fpolitics-features%2Fputin-russia-ukraine-invasion-nazi-operation-1325817%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreviously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Rolling%20Stone.)%20The%20whistleblower%20also%20looked%20into%20claims%20that%20Giuliani%20had%20fraudulently%20raised%20money%20from%20investors%20to%20produce%20a%20never-completed%20film%20about%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20the%20months%20before%20the%202020%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agent's%20reporting%20on%20Giuliani%20wasn't%20received%20well%20in%20the%20bureau's%20New%20York%20field%20office%2C%20his%20statement%20says.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20midst%20of%20my%20reporting%20involving%20Giuliani%2C%20which%20had%20previously%20been%20identified%20by%20my%20supervisor%20as%20'high%20impact%2C'%20my%20management%20told%20me%20they%20received%20a%20call%20from%20a%20supervisor%20in%20%5Bthe%20New%20York%20field%20office%5D%2C%20who%20they%20did%20not%20identify%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20supervisor%20had%20taken%20issue%20with%20my%20reporting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whistleblower%20says%20he%20doesn't%20know%20who%20the%20upset%20supervisor%20was.%20But%20he%20blames%20%26quot%3Ba%20group%20of%20people%20surrounding%20%5BGiuliani%5D%20with%20existing%20or%20historical%20ties%20to%20the%20bureau%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20pattern%20of%20%26quot%3Bretaliatory%20action.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20The%20statement%20points%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffbi-charlie-mcgonigal-labyrinth-oleg-deripaska-russia-trump-allison-guerriero-2023-2%5C%22%3ECharles%20McGonigal%2C%20the%20now-indicted%3C%2Fa%3E%20former%20head%20of%20FBI%20counterintelligence%20in%20New%20York%2C%20as%20one%20possible%20source%20of%20the%20apparent%20%26quot%3Bsuppressive%20efforts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpokespeople%20for%20Giuliani%2C%20Fuks%2C%20and%20Trump%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%3B%20nor%20did%20attorneys%20representing%20Fuks%20and%20McGonigal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI's%20national%20press%20office%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20did%20the%20agent's%20superiors%20order%20them%20to%20stop%20working%20on%20these%20leads%2C%20according%20to%20the%20complaint%20and%20other%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Insider%2C%20they%20also%20ordered%2C%20in%20early%202022%2C%20that%20the%20FBI%20informant%20who%20had%20provided%20the%20best%20intelligence%20on%20Giuliani's%20activities%20be%20%26quot%3Bclosed%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20cut%20off%20from%20further%20FBI%20contact.%20According%20to%20the%20statement%2C%20that%20order%20came%20from%20the%20FBI's%20Foreign%20Influence%20Task%20Force%20or%20FITF%2C%20a%20headquarters-based%20unit%20established%20by%20Director%20Christopher%20Wray%20in%202017%20and%20charged%20with%20combating%20foreign%20influence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20unclear%20how%20much%20of%20the%20friction%20described%20by%20the%20whistleblower's%20statement%20stems%20from%20left%20versus%20right%20as%20opposed%20to%20field%20versus%20headquarters.%20The%20month%20the%20whistleblower's%20bosses%20ordered%20him%20off%20Trumpworld%20investigations%20was%20a%20pivotal%20one%20for%20the%20Bureau's%20investigations%20of%20the%20former%20president.%20On%20August%208%2C%20their%20agents%20executed%20a%20search%20warrant%20on%20Donald%20Trump's%20Mar-a-Lago%20estate%2C%20recovering%20over%20100%20records%20with%20classified%20markings%20that%20would%20become%20key%20evidence%20in%20his%20first%20federal%20indictment%3B%20a%20special%20counsel-led%20prosecution%20led%20to%20a%20second%20Trump%20indictment%20in%20early%20August%20over%20efforts%20to%20overturn%20the%202020%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiuliani%20too%20was%20raided%20by%20the%20FBI%2C%20in%20April%202021%2C%20although%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frudy-giuliani-not-charged-foreign-lobbying-investigation-ukraine-justice-trump-2022-11%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520a%2520court%2520filing%2520Monday%2Csearched%2520his%2520home%2520and%2520office.%5C%22%3Ethat%20probe%20concluded%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20charges%20in%20late%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20before%20the%20agent%20was%20told%20to%20stop%20looking%20at%20Giuliani%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Trump's%20circle%2C%20he%20met%20with%20the%20same%20high-ranking%20supervisor%20to%20pass%20on%20information%20he%20had%20received%20from%20his%20confidential%20sources%20about%20Hunter%20Biden%20and%20his%20ties%20to%20Burisma%2C%20the%20Ukrainian%20energy%20company%20that%20had%20paid%20Hunter%20Biden%20%2483%2C333%20a%20month%20to%20sit%20on%20its%20board.%20%26quot%3BMy%20supervisors%20were%20delighted%20that%20I%20had%20collected%20this%20information%20about%20Burisma%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agent%20wrote%20in%20his%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20agent%20tried%20to%20talk%20about%20what%20their%20sources%20had%20to%20say%20about%20Giuliani%2C%20his%20boss's%20reaction%20was%20very%20different.%20The%20supervisor%20%26quot%3Bforcefully%20interrupted%20me%20and%20ended%20my%20presentation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whistleblower's%20story%20offers%20a%20different%20perspective%20than%20the%20one%20laid%20out%20by%20three%20other%20FBI%20whistleblowers%20who%20testified%20before%20the%20GOP-led%20Select%20Subcommittee%20on%20the%20Weaponization%20of%20the%20Federal%20Government%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20have%20admitted%20accepting%20financial%20support%20from%20right-wing%20groups.%20Those%20whistleblowers%20complained%20that%20the%20bureau%20was%20biased%20%3Cem%3Eagainst%3C%2Fem%3E%20Trump%20and%20his%20supporters%2C%20that%20the%20crackdown%20on%20January%206%20insurrectionists%20went%20too%20far%2C%20and%20that%20they%20had%20faced%20retaliation%20from%20the%20bureau%20for%20their%20conservative%20views.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20interview%20with%20Insider%2C%20the%20new%20whistleblower%20said%20that%20he%20had%20approached%20the%20GOP%20subcommittee%2C%20led%20by%20Rep.%20Jim%20Jordan.%20But%20when%20the%20subcommittee's%20staff%20learned%20from%20the%20whistleblower%20that%20the%20Hunter%20Biden%20information%20had%20been%20handled%20appropriately%2C%20their%20interest%20dwindled%2C%20the%20whistleblower%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20FBI%20made%20a%20diligent%20attempt%20to%20run%20the%20Biden%20material%20to%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20whistleblower%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20slow-played.%20Chairman%20Jordan%20should%20not%20be%20using%20this%20as%20an%20example%20to%20show%20that%20the%20FBI%20is%20biased%20against%20the%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussell%20Dye%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Jordan%2C%20denied%20the%20whistleblower's%20allegations%20that%20the%20committee%20was%20cherry-picking%20witnesses%20who%20claimed%20to%20be%20able%20to%20implicate%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20would%20under%20no%20circumstance%20ever%20tell%20a%20whistleblower%20that%20we%20weren't%20interested%20in%20their%20story%2C%26quot%3B%20Dye%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20had%20plenty%20of%20whistleblowers%20come%20forward%20about%20issues%20not%20relating%20to%20the%20President.%26quot%3B%20Dye%20said%20the%20committee%20was%20still%20weighing%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20information%20that%20the%20whistleblower%20had%20given%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20the%20emergence%20of%20this%20new%20whistleblower%2C%20there%20has%20been%20ample%20evidence%20of%20individual%20FBI%20agents%20with%20pro-Trump%20partisan%20sympathies.%20Jared%20Wise%2C%20an%20FBI%20supervisor%20who%20left%20the%20bureau%20in%202017%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fusao-dc%2Fpr%2Fformer-fbi-supervisory-special-agent-indicted-federal-court-felony-charges-related-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20now%20stands%20accused%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20joining%20the%20insurrectionists%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20breaking%20into%20the%20Capitol%2C%20and%20shouting%20%26quot%3Bkill%20'em!%20Kill%20'em!%26quot%3B%20as%20rioters%20as%20they%20attacked%20the%20Capitol%20Police%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurther%20up%20the%20chain%20of%20command%2C%20bureau%20leadership%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20intimidated%20by%20Trump's%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20state%26quot%3B%20rhetoric%20and%20his%20treatment%20of%20former%20senior%20FBI%20personnel%20like%20James%20Comey%20and%20Peter%20Strzok%20%E2%80%94%20has%20resisted%20investigating%20the%20former%20president.%20A%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F06%2F19%2Ffbi-resisted-opening-probe-into-trumps-role-jan-6-more-than-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Washington%20Post%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20more%20than%20a%20year%20passed%20before%20the%20bureau%20formally%20opened%20a%20probe%20into%20connections%20between%20the%20Trump%20White%20House%20and%20the%20January%206%20violence.%20Other%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2023%2F03%2F01%2Ffbi-dispute-trump-mar-a-lago-raid%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20reporting%20by%20the%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20senior%20FBI%20officials%20attempted%20to%20push%20back%20on%20plans%20by%20Justice%20Department%20prosecutors%20to%20search%20Mar-a-Lago%20without%20Trump's%20permission.%20Some%20FBI%20agents%20were%20reportedly%20satisfied%20by%20an%20assertion%20made%20by%20Trump's%20legal%20team%20that%20he'd%20turned%20over%20all%20his%20classified%20documents%2C%20and%20wanted%20to%20close%20the%20Mar-a-Lago%20government%20records%20investigation%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FBI%20is%20ideologically%20diverse%20and%20decentralized%2C%20with%2035%2C000%20employees%20spread%20out%20across%2056%20field%20offices%20from%20Anchorage%20to%20San%20Juan.%20The%20glimpse%20of%20one%20field%20office%20provided%20by%20the%20new%20whistleblower%20could%20be%20more%20indicative%20of%20a%20risk-averse%20bureaucracy%20struggling%20to%20balance%20its%20law-enforcement%20duties%20with%20its%20increasingly%20fragile%20public%20image%20than%20a%20politically%20motivated%20cover-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whistleblower%20recounts%20how%20one%20of%20his%20sources%2C%20code-named%20Genius%2C%20had%20won%20the%20trust%20of%20racist%20extremists%20whom%20the%20bureau%20investigated%20for%20their%20role%20in%20the%20January%206%20violence.%20Genius%20was%20able%20to%20do%20so%20because%20he%20had%20credibility%20on%20the%20far-right%20political%20fringe.%20Nevertheless%2C%20the%20whistleblower%20claims%2C%20the%20FBI%20ordered%20that%20the%20source%20be%20closed%2C%20supposedly%20for%20making%20the%20same%20kinds%20of%20%26quot%3Binappropriate%26quot%3B%20comments%20on%20social%20media%20that%20had%20earned%20him%20access%20to%20some%20of%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20insurrection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agent's%20decision%20to%20make%20a%20formal%20statement%20to%20Congress%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20a%20last%20resort.%20He%20previously%20approached%20the%20FBI's%20internal%20ombudsman%20with%20his%20concerns.%20In%20December%202021%2C%20he%20submitted%20an%20official%20whistleblower%20complaint%20to%20the%20head%20of%20his%20field%20office.%20Under%20federal%20law%2C%20that%20complaint%20should%20have%20protected%20him%20from%20internal%20reprisals.%20But%20according%20to%20his%20account%2C%20his%20superiors%20responded%20with%20punishments%2C%20disciplining%20him%20for%20errors%20in%20paperwork%20and%20reassigning%20him%20to%20a%20new%20post%20outside%20of%20his%20longtime%20area%20of%20expertise%2C%20one%20that%20required%20a%20multi-hour%20commute%20from%20his%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20experiences%2C%20he%20told%20Insider%2C%20are%20part%20of%20what%20compelled%20them%20to%20share%20what%20he%20knows%20with%20Congress%2C%20not%20to%20harm%20the%20FBI%20but%20to%20improve%20and%20correct%20public%20misperceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20people%20in%20the%20FBI%20who%20are%20biased%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20robots.%20But%20the%20bureau%20itself%20has%20integrity.%20It's%20necessary.%20Despite%20the%20scars%20that%20I%20bear%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20colleagues%20are%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMattathias%20Schwartz%20is%20Insider's%20chief%20national%20security%20correspondent.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20by%20email%20at%20schwartz79%40protonmail.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffbi-whistleblower-senate-judiciary-russia-giuliani-leak-trump-allies-fuks-biden-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691612340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64d3ec0e4dd2b50019c244df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffbi-whistleblower-senate-judiciary-russia-giuliani-leak-trump-allies-fuks-biden-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20FBI%20agent's%20bombshell%20allegations%20of%20political%20bias%20appeared%20in%20a%20leaked%20statement%20made%20to%20the%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mschwartz%40businessinsider.com%20(Mattathias%20Schwartz)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A735%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffbi-whistleblower-senate-judiciary-russia-giuliani-leak-trump-allies-fuks-biden-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20to%20tighten%20rules%20on%20outbound%20investments%20to%20China%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691611804000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto