3E%20to%20protest%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20unavailability%20to%20discuss%20the%20Manipur%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversial%20Bill%20was%20passed%20by%20voice%20vote%2C%20a%20method%20by%20which%20legislators%20vote%20on%20Bills%20by%20calling%20out%20%E2%80%98aye%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELegislators%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20first%20cleared%20the%20Bill%20on%20Monday%20(August%207).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnion%20information%20technology%20minister%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%20criticised%20the%20opposition%20for%20not%20being%20present%20to%20debate%20the%20Bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20would%20have%20been%20good%20had%20the%20opposition%20discussed%20the%20Bill%20today%20%5Bin%20the%20House%5D.%20But%20no%20opposition%20leader%20or%20member%20is%20concerned%20over%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20citizens%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Bill%20was%20tabled%20in%20parliament%20after%20extensive%20public%20consultation%2C%20although%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Ffalling-short-the-hindu-editorial-on-the-digital-data-protection-bill-2023%2Farticle67173250.ece%5C%22%3Edoubts%20have%20been%20raised%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20transparency%20of%20that%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20says%20the%20Bill%20will%20protect%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20Indian%20citizens%20and%20introduce%20important%20regulations%20on%20how%20their%20personal%20data%20is%20processed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20critics%20of%20the%20proposed%20legislation%20say%20it%20exempts%20the%20Union%20government%20too%20broadly%20from%20the%20consequences%20of%20how%20it%20processes%20this%20data%2C%20and%20that%20its%20provisions%20may%20dilute%20India%E2%80%99s%20existing%20right%20to%20information%20(RTI)%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwill-the-data-protection-law-empower-the-public%5C%22%3ETen%20Reasons%20Why%20The%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Law%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Empower%20Citizens%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20the%20Bill%20was%20cleared%20by%20parliament%2C%20the%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20said%20the%20Bill%20%E2%80%9Cprioritises%20%E2%80%A6%20a%20regime%20that%20facilitates%20the%20processing%20of%20personal%20data%20by%20state%20and%20private%20actors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThe%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%2C%202023%20is%20closer%20to%20becoming%20the%20Digital%20Personal%20Data%20Protection%20Act%2C%202023%2C%20having%20been%20passed%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20We%20are%20disappointed%20with%20the%20version%20of%20the%20Bill%20that%20may%20ultimately%20become%20India%E2%80%99s%20data%20protection%20legislation.%201%2F3%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FUkcZhWMpQv%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FUkcZhWMpQv%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Internet%20Freedom%20Foundation%20(IFF)%20(%40internetfreedom)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Finternetfreedom%2Fstatus%2F1689257556747730944%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EAugust%209%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fgovernment-severely-restricting-rti-act-through-data-bill-ncpri%2Farticle67080300.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%20in%20July%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20while%20current%20RTI%20laws%20allow%20for%20personal%20information%20to%20be%20disclosed%20under%20its%20ambit%20if%20its%20release%20is%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20Data%20Protection%20Bill%20removes%20this%20caveat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20organisation%20called%20the%20National%20Campaign%20for%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Right%20to%20Information%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fregressive-amendments-to-rti-act-ncpri-flags-concerns-over-digital-personal-data-protection-bill%5C%22%3Ecautioned%20against%20this%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20August%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20well%20established%20that%20access%20to%20granular%20information%2C%20including%20personal%20information%2C%20is%20critical%20to%20empower%20people%20to%20undertake%20collective%20monitoring%20and%20ensure%20they%20are%20able%20to%20access%20their%20rights%20and%20entitlements%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20principle%20is%20well%20recognised%20and%20has%20been%20adopted%20in%20various%20welfare%20programs%20and%20schemes.%20The%20proposed%20Bill%20will%20potentially%20place%20impediments%20and%20restrictions%20on%20such%20public%20disclosures.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJournalist%20groups%20have%20also%20raised%20fears%20that%20the%20Bill%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fdigital-personal-data-protection-bill-adverse-impact-press-freedom-editors-guild%5C%22%3Eenable%20censorship%20of%20their%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20and%20DIGIPUB%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20August%206%20that%20the%20Bill%20could%20be%20used%20to%20widen%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20existing%20powers%20of%20censorship%2C%20because%20Clause%2037(1)(b)%20will%20allow%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccensor%20content%20on%20vague%20and%20unspecified%20grounds%20%E2%80%98in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20general%20public%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1691607956000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F09234852%2FData-protection-bill-in-rajya-sabha.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fparliament-clears-data-protection-bill-amid-opposition-w