20youth%20from%20over%20a%20dozen%20districts%2C%20including%20Jalandhar%2C%20Hoshiarpur%2C%20Kapurthala%2C%20Nawanshahr%2C%20Amritsar%2C%20Ludhiana%2C%20Moga%2C%20Ferozepur%2C%20Faridkot%20and%20Muktsar%20reached%20the%20site.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20moment%20we%20saw%20a%20message%20by%20Baba%20Seechewal%20to%20reach%20the%20flooded%20site%20at%20Lohian%20Khas%20village%20in%20the%20Shahkot%20subdivision%20of%20Jalandhar%20for%20sewa%2C%20we%20rushed%20there%20with%20mud-loaded%20tractor%20trolleys.%20We%20also%20brought%20fodder%20for%20milch%20animals%2C%20who%20were%20the%20worst%20affected%20in%20the%20floods%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Amrik%20Singh%20and%20his%20friends%2C%20who%20travelled%20from%20Zira%20in%20Ferozepur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192941%2Febcdf01a-fd66-4391-8817-6b7ad3e271b2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192941%2Febcdf01a-fd66-4391-8817-6b7ad3e271b2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192941%2Febcdf01a-fd66-4391-8817-6b7ad3e271b2-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192941%2Febcdf01a-fd66-4391-8817-6b7ad3e271b2-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667396%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EVolunteers%20fill%20sacks%20of%20mud%20in%20iron%20meshes%20to%20plug%20breaches%20in%20the%20Sutlej%20river%20embankment.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERow%20over%20Punjab%20drainage%20department%E2%80%99s%20letter%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%E2%80%99s%20effort%20received%20praise%20from%20the%20people%2C%C2%A0the%20Punjab%20drainage%20department%20issued%20a%20letter%20which%20claimed%20that%20Baba%20Seechewal%20was%20interfering%20in%20its%20work.%20The%20letter%20became%20a%20matter%20of%20embarrassment%20for%20the%20Punjab%20government%2C%20forcing%20it%20to%20remain%20tight-lipped%20while%20Baba%20Seechewal%20continued%20the%20repair%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKulvinder%20Singh%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20flood%20control%20committee%20of%20the%20area%20near%20the%20Sutlej%20River%20breaches%2C%20said%20that%20the%20drainage%20department%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20remove%20the%20silt%20properly%20from%20the%20water%20channels%20of%20the%20Sutlej%20River%20caused%20the%20flood.%20This%20resulted%20in%20the%20flooding%20of%2054%20villages%20of%20Jalandhar%20and%20Kapurthala%20districts%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%E2%80%99s%20lives%20were%20affected%20and%20more%20than%201%2C000%20acres%20of%20paddy%20crop%20was%20damaged%20too.%20Firstly%2C%20the%20drainage%20department%20failed%20to%20act%20properly%20on%20time.%20Then%2C%20to%20cover%20up%20their%20inefficiency%2C%20they%20issued%20a%20letter%20against%20Baba%20Seechewal%2C%20which%20did%20not%20go%20down%20well%20with%20the%20public%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20The%20drainage%20department%20should%20be%20thankful%20to%20Baba%20Seechewal%20that%20the%20work%20was%20completed%20in%20such%20a%20short%20span%20of%20time%20and%20that%20too%20without%20any%20burden%20on%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20expenses%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20the%20letter%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Chindrance%E2%80%9D%20caused%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20the%20executive%20engineer%20(XEN)%20of%20the%20Drainage%20and%20Mining%20Department%2C%20Amarinder%20Singh%20Pandher%2C%20dodged%20the%20query.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CUsually%20there%20are%20hindrances%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20any%20work%20but%20everything%20is%20resolved%20now.%20There%20was%20no%20such%20issue.%20The%20target%20was%20to%20complete%20the%20work%20and%20we%20have%20achieved%20that.%20We%20were%20working%20on%20the%20downward%20stream%20construction%20while%20Baba%20Seechewal%20was%20leading%20the%20upward%20stream%20work.%E2%80%9D%20He%20refused%20to%20comment%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhalid%20Mohammed%2C%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Panjab%20University%20in%20Chandigarh%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20ideally%2C%20it%20is%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20responsibility%20to%20oversee%20the%20relief%20and%20rescue%20work.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20should%20conduct%20a%20timely%20survey%20of%20the%20rivers%20and%20water%20channels.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20government%20has%20fewer%20resources%2C%20then%20there%20is%20no%20harm%20in%20working%20in%20coordination%20with%20social%20workers%20or%20public%20figures%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20letter%20that%20accused%20Baba%20Seechewal%20of%20interference%2C%20Mohammed%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20it%20was%20too%20much.%20Baba%20Seechewal%20is%20a%20public%20figure%20and%20he%20has%20been%20working%20for%20public%20causes.%20Even%20if%20there%20was%20an%20issue%2C%20the%20officer%20could%20have%20brought%20it%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20Punjab%20government.%20Issuing%20a%20letter%20and%20making%20it%20public%20was%20wrong.%20Such%20incidents%20discourage%20other%20good%20Samaritans%20from%20working%20with%20the%20government%20and%20for%20public%20causes.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EContributions%20from%20various%20persons%2C%20big%20and%20small%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20volunteer%20effort%20received%20support%20from%20several%20good%20Samaritans%2C%20including%20high-profile%20persons%20and%20ordinary%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJalandhar-based%20former%20cricketer%20Harbhajan%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20AAP%2C%20and%20the%20Canada-based%20NRI%20Manpreet%20Singh%20gifted%20tractors%20to%20Baba%20Seechewal%20to%20expedite%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20raised%20mud%20embankment%20and%20rescue%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192924%2F5457d722-2a39-42f1-95fc-914e550b7be9.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192924%2F5457d722-2a39-42f1-95fc-914e550b7be9.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192924%2F5457d722-2a39-42f1-95fc-914e550b7be9-300x162.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192924%2F5457d722-2a39-42f1-95fc-914e550b7be9-1024x554.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667394%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22649%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJalandhar-based%20former%20cricketer%20Harbhajan%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20AAP%2C%20donated%20a%20tractor%20to%20aid%20the%20volunteer%20work.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20Delhi-based%20acclaimed%20Punjabi%20writer%20Ajeet%20Caur%20and%20her%20daughter%20Arpana%20Caur%2C%20who%20is%20known%20for%20her%20iconic%20paintings%2C%20donated%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20Baba%20Seechewal%20to%20buy%20an%20excavator%20machine%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20Rs%2057%20lakh.%20Baba%20Seechewal%20also%20donated%20Rs%208.50%20lakh%20from%20his%20salary%20and%20arranged%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20money%20on%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20doctors%E2%80%99%20association%20from%20Moga%20district%20donated%202%2C000%20litres%20of%20diesel%20worth%20Rs%202%20lakh%20for%20hassle-free%20work%20at%20the%20raised%20embankment.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20villagers%20and%20NRIs%20from%20Dosanjh%20Kalan%20village%20in%20Jalandhar%20%E2%80%93%20the%20native%20village%20of%20Punjabi%20singer%20Diljit%20Dosanjh%20%E2%80%93%20also%20donated%202%2C200%20litres%20of%20diesel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20many%20ordinary%20people%20who%20made%20significant%20donations%20from%20their%20own%20pockets.%20%E2%80%9CTwo%20youths%20from%20Amritsar%20brought%2010%20litres%20of%20diesel%20for%20the%20repair%20work.%20It%20is%20this%20spirit%2C%20which%20motivated%20others%20to%20participate%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20volunteer%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Baba%20Seechewal%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDriving%20an%20excavator%2C%20Baba%20Seechewal%E2%80%99s%20call%20to%20plug%20the%20gaps%20received%20a%20thumping%20response%20within%20hours%20on%20July%2011.%20The%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%2C%20known%20for%20his%20simple%20and%20cost-effective%20methods%20to%20protect%20the%20environment%2C%20heads%20the%20Nirmal%20Kuteya%20Ek%20Onkar%20Charitable%20Trust%20at%20Seechewal%20village%2C%20Jalandhar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20been%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20make%20environmental%20issues%20a%20public%20subject.%20Among%20his%20previous%20efforts%20are%20clearing%20the%20once-polluted%20holy%20Kali%20Bein%20rivulet%2C%20a%20tributary%20of%20Beas%20River%20where%20the%20founder%20of%20Sikhism%20Guru%20Nanak%20Dev%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20gained%20enlightenment%20and%20managing%20wastewater%20management%20and%20planting%20native%20trees%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20Punjab.%20Baba%20Seechewal%20also%20appeared%20as%20one%20of%20%3Cem%3ETime%3C%2Fem%3E%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Heroes%20of%20the%20Environment%E2%80%99%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Baba%20Seechewal%20said%20that%20the%20way%20people%2C%20especially%20the%20youth%2C%20joined%20hands%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20voluntary%20service%20was%20remarkable.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20came%20from%20those%20villages%20whose%20names%20we%20had%20never%20heard%20of.%20It%20was%20reassuring%20to%20see%20that%20Punjab%E2%80%99s%20youth%20are%20connected%20to%20their%20roots%20and%20remain%20motivated.%20If%20the%20youth%E2%80%99s%20energy%20is%20channelled%2C%20they%20can%20achieve%20anything%20%E2%80%93%20all%20they%20need%20is%20direction%20in%20life.%20We%20are%20thankful%20to%20the%20almighty%20for%20the%20successful%20completion%20of%20the%20repair%20work%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20MP%20said.%20He%20said%20that%20there%20was%20more%20work%20to%20be%20done%2C%20to%20raise%20the%20level%20of%20embankment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmrik%20Singh%20Sandhu%2C%20a%20volunteer%20who%20was%20continuing%20to%20work%20at%20the%20flood%20site%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%2018%20days%20consecutively%2C%20we%20worked%20in%20three%20shifts%20for%2020%20hours%20a%20day.%20We%20used%20to%20begin%20work%20at%206%3A30%20am%20and%20would%20continue%20till%20midnight.%20Youth%2C%20women%20and%20the%20elderly%20played%20a%20big%20role%20in%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20embankment.%20After%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protest%20%5Bin%202020%20and%202021%20against%20the%20three%20central%20farm%20laws%5D%2C%20this%20is%20yet%20another%20example%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20participation%20working%20wonders.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192908%2F74e55aea-0c09-4a99-abd0-eea70d7a0a93.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192908%2F74e55aea-0c09-4a99-abd0-eea70d7a0a93.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192908%2F74e55aea-0c09-4a99-abd0-eea70d7a0a93-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F09192908%2F74e55aea-0c09-4a99-abd0-eea70d7a0a93-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-667393%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPeople%20from%20all%20walks%20of%20life%20participated%20in%20the%20effort.%20Photo%3A%20By%20arrangement%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWord%20spread%20through%20social%20media%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%2C%20especially%20Instagram%2C%20WhatsApp%20and%20Facebook%2C%20emerged%20as%20the%20major%20platforms%20for%20spreading%20the%20word%20about%20voluntary%20service%20among%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstagram%20was%20flooded%20with%20reels%20showing%20people%20working%20tirelessly%20to%20plug%20the%20breach%20in%20the%20river%2C%20which%20motivated%20others%20to%20follow%20suit.%20Such%20was%20the%20enthusiasm%20to%20contribute%20that%20mud-loaded%20tractors%20remained%20parked%20in%20a%20serpentine%20queue%20at%20the%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20pertinent%20to%20mention%20that%20a%20single%20tractor%20filled%20with%20mud%20costs%20around%20Rs%202%2C500%2C%20while%20Rs%206%2C000%20was%20spent%20on%20filling%20diesel.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20collective%20decision%20of%20all%20the%20nearby%20villages%20to%20contribute%20money%20and%20help%20Baba%20Seechewal%20in%20plugging%20the%20breaches%20in%20the%20Sutlej.%20So%20far%2C%20we%20have%20brought%20over%20100%20tractors%20loaded%20with%20mud%20to%20the%20repair%20site.%20We%20are%20still%20bringing%20tractors%20every%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Tony%20Sandhu%2C%20from%20the%20Youth%20Football%20Club%20(YFC)%2C%20Rurka%20Kalan%20village%2C%20Jalandhar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20farmers%20from%20Faridkot%20said%20that%20after%20they%20shared%20a%20post%20on%20WhatsApp%20about%20the%20requirement%20of%20mud%20for%20the%20repair%20work%2C%